{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YW21fYW4ZUiPKjuvNBq2az","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. The seed job used the management API on port 15672 with the `rabbitmq-blue-admin` credentials (user: `admin`, password: `adminpass`), but it accessed it from WITHIN the cluster using the internal service name `http://rabbitmq-blue:15672/api`.\n\nThe issue with my curl command is that the k8s proxy is stripping the `Authorization` header before forwarding to the RabbitMQ management API, because the k8s proxy itself is receiving an unauthorized request (it doesn't need auth for the API proxy path, but perhaps the python-based proxy implementation is intercepting auth).\nActually, looking at the verbose output more carefully, that 401 response with the Python BaseHTTP server header is coming from the KARMA proxy itself, not RabbitMQ. The proxy is rejecting the request before it even gets forwarded. Let me try sending the request without any credentials to see if that's what the proxy expects.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2650,"cache_read_input_tokens":39061,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2650},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"972f2e5d-1f65-49de-bc8b-cfff6a704196","uuid":"007a0c33-5dd0-4ba4-aa86-91b30cdbeac6","request_id":"req_011CbxUy5CAeD8E5jKyoooiu"}
