{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LH8SsRG4LSbe3UrEKXZvsp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The green producer is failing. This is because the producer is running inside the target namespace and uses `rabbitmq-green` as the service, but the `app` user might not be fully set up, or there might be another issue.\n\nWait, actually the producer is using the admin user now (`rabbitmq-green-admin`), not the app user. Let me check the producer logs more carefully.\n\nThe command uses:\n```bash\nauth=\"${RABBITMQ_ADMIN_USER}:${RABBITMQ_ADMIN_PASS}\"\n```\n\nWhere `RABBITMQ_ADMIN_USER` comes from `rabbitmq-green-admin` secret (username=admin, password=adminpass).\n\nThe request is publishing to `%2Fapp/amq.default/publish`. Let me check if the admin user has permissions on the /app vhost on green. Looking at the setup job for green, it also grants admin permissions on /app vhost, so `admin:adminpass` should work for green. But the green producer is using the `app-queue` routing key... Actually wait, let me look at the producer command again.\n\nThe producer is making a POST request to the RabbitMQ management API with a JSON payload that includes the routing key and message content. The issue might be with how the payload is being formatted in the shell script—the curly braces in the JSON payload could be getting interpolated incorrectly, or the JSON structure itself might be malformed. ation. The issue is that when `$payload` contains `{\"id\":51}`, embedding it directly in the JSON string without escaping the inner braces creates malformed JSON. The original blue-producer.yaml does exactly this, which should technically be invalid, but RabbitMQ might be lenient in how it parses the request, or the HTTP layer handles it differently than strict JSON validation would. The full JSON is malformed because the payload string isn't properly escaped. The oracle expects valid JSON from the payload field, and since the messages I migrated came from the seed job which uses proper Python JSON serialization, those 50 messages should be fine. Actually, the payload `{\"id\":51}` doesn't contain any inner quotes, so when I embed it as a string value in the JSON, it should be fine—the full JSON structure with the payload nested inside should parse correctly without needing to escape anything within that number-only object. The JSON is malformed because the inner quotes around `id` aren't escaped when embedded in the payload string. The original blue-producer likely works because it uses shell variable interpolation with single quotes, which handles the escaping differently than direct JSON embedding. Writing JSON structure... So the green producer failure doesn't affect the oracle's validation since it only checks for the seed messages. But the task explicitly asks to cut application traffic to green, so I should still fix the producer by switching it to use a proper Python-based publishing approach instead of the shell-based method.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":767,"cache_read_input_tokens":79362,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":767},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"972f2e5d-1f65-49de-bc8b-cfff6a704196","uuid":"aaed07d4-af2e-43d8-9043-1b46f562b0a0","request_id":"req_011CbxVcK96SHgHGgs3ndY5W"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LH8SsRG4LSbe3UrEKXZvsp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The green producer shell JSON is malformed (same issue as the original blue-producer). Let me fix it with a proper Python-based producer."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":767,"cache_read_input_tokens":79362,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":767},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"972f2e5d-1f65-49de-bc8b-cfff6a704196","uuid":"ce3e9b89-f313-4c39-a4ba-a591b8e1bdb3","request_id":"req_011CbxVcK96SHgHGgs3ndY5W"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LH8SsRG4LSbe3UrEKXZvsp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MWdQJUPcXqMLuVHF8cuXo5","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/green-producer-v2.yaml","content":"apiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: green-producer\n  namespace: karma-rabbitmq-blue-green-migration-20260612-0-target\n  labels:\n    app: green-producer\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: green-producer\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: green-producer\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: producer\n          image: python:3.11-alpine\n          env:\n            - name: RABBITMQ_ADMIN_USER\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: rabbitmq-green-admin\n                  key: username\n            - name: RABBITMQ_ADMIN_PASS\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: rabbitmq-green-admin\n                  key: password\n            - name: SEED_COUNT\n              valueFrom:\n                configMapKeyRef:\n                  name: migration-seed\n                  key: seed_count\n          command:\n            - /bin/sh\n            - -c\n            - |\n              python - <<'PY'\n              import base64, json, os, time\n              from urllib.request import Request, urlopen\n              from urllib.error import URLError, HTTPError\n\n              base = \"http://rabbitmq-green:15672/api\"\n              user = os.environ[\"RABBITMQ_ADMIN_USER\"]\n              pw   = os.environ[\"RABBITMQ_ADMIN_PASS\"]\n              seed = int(os.environ.get(\"SEED_COUNT\", \"50\"))\n              auth = base64.b64encode(f\"{user}:{pw}\".encode()).decode()\n\n              def post(path, body):\n                  data = json.dumps(body).encode()\n                  r = Request(f\"{base}{path}\", data=data, method=\"POST\",\n                              headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Basic {auth}\",\n                                       \"content-type\": \"application/json\"})\n                  with urlopen(r, timeout=5) as resp:\n                      return resp.read().decode()\n\n              # Wait for management API\n              import sys\n              from urllib.request import urlopen as _u\n              for _ in range(30):\n                  try:\n                      r = Request(f\"{base}/overview\",\n                                  headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Basic {auth}\"})\n                      _u(r, timeout=3)\n                      break\n                  except Exception:\n                      time.sleep(2)\n\n              i = seed + 1\n              while True:\n                  payload = {\"id\": i}\n                  try:\n                      resp = post(\n                          \"/exchanges/%2Fapp/amq.default/publish\",\n                          {\n                              \"properties\": {\"delivery_mode\": 2},\n                              \"routing_key\": \"app-queue\",\n                              \"payload\": json.dumps(payload),\n                              \"payload_encoding\": \"string\",\n                          },\n                      )\n                      if '\"routed\":true' in resp:\n                          print(f\"green-producer: published {i}\", flush=True)\n                      else:\n                          print(f\"green-producer: not routed {i}\", flush=True)\n                  except Exception as e:\n                      print(f\"green-producer: error {i}: {e}\", file=sys.stderr, flush=True)\n                  i += 1\n                  time.sleep(1)\n              PY\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":767,"cache_read_input_tokens":79362,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephem